From e946d8b1f90ddcdbc3a5a3df5d5f57bc48f5476b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vasu Bhatia <git@vbh.ai>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 15:53:55 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] eink: e-ink themed Center overlay with auto-brightness pill

Replace the mixed-grey Center overlay with a pure black/white EPD-friendly
theme. All controls use a state-list pill background that flips white-bg
with 2dp black stroke (default) to solid black (selected/pressed), paired
with a companion text-color selector so the foreground flips in step.

UI changes:
- Header reduced to title + settings gear + close. The settings gear deep-
  links to the Settings EinkSettingsFragment via SubSettings.
- New row beneath the header holds two equal-weight pills: AUTO ON/OFF
  and LIGHTS ON/OFF.
- Each light row is a single line: vector icon (snowflake / sun / keyboard,
  filled when on, hollow when off) on the left, then chevron steppers
  flanking the percentage value. Tapping the icon toggles that light.
- Step buttons render double/single chevrons mirrored via scaleX=-1.
- Refresh-mode and preset buttons reuse the same pill background; the old
  per-button setTint logic is replaced by setSelected so the state-list
  drives the visual.

Behavior:
- AUTO pill toggles SCREEN_BRIGHTNESS_MODE; the existing
  EinkAutoBrightnessController already observes that key and starts/stops
  the curve accordingly.
- Master LIGHTS pill: turning it off while auto is on snapshots the auto
  state in eink_auto_was_on, forces auto off so the lights actually stay
  dark, then snapshots and zeros each currently-on light. Turning the
  master back on restores each light from its snapshot and, if the flag
  is set, re-enables auto. Manual auto-toggle via the AUTO pill does not
  set the flag, so the auto-restore is scoped strictly to the master
  round-trip.
- Settings.System SCREEN_BRIGHTNESS_MODE observer keeps the AUTO pill in
  sync if auto is changed elsewhere while the overlay is visible.

Change-Id: I51710a22c70fe40aa3e317a9a2e8d611e3c4be3d
